When @dugmcc sets his mind on something he will get it done. Even if it means to grow a caveman-like beard for extra power ...

Deep Blue Sea (VHard) at the Black Cave, Manly

What a fun evening out. Thanks @dugmcc for the stellar performance, @weebitwindy for crawling into a muddy cave to get the light into the prime position, @jake_bresnehan for pushing my skills to the limits to match his iphone photo, @shayb152 for the patience with out #nightphotography shenanigans, @ange_malysheva and @davidkvas for making me laugh so much that even falling of everything felt like fun!

node.text:
Good Evening Everyone. 
It's Lorie @lilmissylilmissy here, featuring some final extraordinary highlights selected from our Saturday  theme this week. Glad to be here with you all! 
.
Theme: “STRIDE BY”
.
Tag #jj_forum_3100 .
Photographer: 📸 @stoptheroc 

This delightful architectural gem  and intriguing #strideby image was captured and shared today by @stoptheroc and it was first initially found and featured by @jj_editor_elkunia in our special editor’s highlighted hand picked selections from the associated theme’s tag of the day. @jjcommunity tag. Thank you Elzbieta for the assist @jj_editor_elkunia 

👏👏 - Please Everyone, do feel welcome to help congratulate, celebrate, and support @stoptheroc with some supportive feedback, comments, and/or go visit this photographer’s individual account and give a new follow and IG friend.  #createtoconnect 

.
I’ll be back super soon with the last final highlights for this theme.
Thanks again for joining in today everyone! 
I really have loved and adored all of your pictures everyone! Thank you for sharing such awesome pictures and images today here,with us and within this communal realm of some most loving and supportive creative voices, friendly photographers, and passionate artists from all over the globe. You all make this community extremely special and a joy to be a part of. 
Stay tuned.
With Love and Gratitude, 
-Lorie @lilmissylilmissy / 
@jj_editor_lorie

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Anna Davey on September 26, 2020 tagging @scarpa_australia. Image may contain: shoes, text that says 'FURIAS'.

node.text: I get alot of shoe questions. For me shoes have always been such a personal thing and what's right for one person isn't right for another generally. Furia S is always my personal favourite yet it's not often I have them as I climb so much they don't last long. I get a longer life out of the Drago so I usually wear those. Climbing these days is so volume based and the softness of these just perform the best for me but people heavier than me, say @tomkaskow can't wear these and he actually feels like the VSR is soft, whereas I can't seem to get enough weight through them. Anyway, I broke these in yesterday and boy it feels good to be back in them! ❤️ Ask me your shoe questions here 💪 @scarpa_australia
@anna.davey will be mostly indoor and grit stone

node.text: For the best homemade applesauce: Choose the right apple, don't peel it, and add nothing more than sugar and water. It's that simple. 🍎 Recipe link in bio.
Perhaps a little cinnamon or nutmeg!

If you pick the right apple combination, sugar isn’t needed.  If I have cider on hand, I add that rather than water. I love canning my own applesauce. It’s one of the easiest things to preserve that way!

node.text: Photo by @erintrieb / Left to Right: Tiye Curry, Tyra DuBose, and Taylor Hardges protest with the Black Lives Matter movement in Detroit, Michigan, in June. Over three months have passed since protests broke out across the United States, with demonstrators demanding justice for the death of George Floyd and an end to police brutality against African Americans. Protests continue in cities like Portland and Kenosha, Wisconsin, after the shooting of Jacob Blake. Follow @erintrieb for more human stories from around the world.
